  "grammar_point": {
    "title": "Telling time with 点 (diǎn) and 分 (fēn)",
    "explanation": "To tell the time: [number] + 点 (o'clock) + [minutes] + 分. For half past, use 半 (bàn). Note: for '2 o'clock', Chinese uses 两 (liǎng) instead of 二 (èr) when counting things. Time expressions go at the start or right after the subject.",
